entries.femaleVariant: Leave the boy out of this, please.
Start talking.
Fuck you.
I-I... I was just looking for uh…
Scram, kiddo.
What're you doing here, Tommie?
You should leave.
Hi, Tommie. My name's V. Whatcha doin' here?
Your day'll come. Just takes time, that's all.
Uhh... Nothin... I'm just kinda... H-here…?
How much do you make from these contracts?
What in the--
Darn it... It's gotta be here... it's-it's gotta...
Hey, lighten up, kiddo. You're too big to be crying.
Tommie! Out, now!
No need to get emotional. Uh, let's be professional about this…
Shut up and grant me access.
We'll do the leak.
Fuck your offer.
Tommie…
Shouldn't be in here, kid.
I know, I know... You won't tell Miss Fiona, right?
What's Fiona like?
I'm no snitch.
[Sit] You'll get chosen some day.
Can't always win in life, Tommie.
What do you want in life?
Can't always win in life, y'know.
Do you know where Fiona's terminal is?
[Stand] Gotta take care of something.
Say, little whiz like you wouldn't know where Fiona's terminal is, would ya? Need it for a sec.
It's right there, can't you see?
Was nice meetin' ya, Tommie, but I've got some biz to take care of.
Well would ya look at that. Silly ol' me.
See? I know everything!
But then I'll lose. And then everyone'll laugh at me.
W-wait, she was just looking for your office! Uh, I was just trying to help! Please, Miss Fiona!
entries.maleVariant: W-wait, h-he was looking for your office! I was just trying to help! Please, Miss Fiona!

entries.femaleVariant: This Miss Fiona – what's she like?
She's tough, b-but it's only so that we become top athletes with uh, um…  prospects! Yeah…
That what you were looking for in these drawers? Prospects?
[Stand] Chin up.
Now buck up and get outta here 'fore Miss Fiona sees you.
Won't say anythin' if you delta quick.
Shouldn't be in here, kid. Go on, scram.
Start talkin', and it better make sense.
I'll make you a counter-offer.
Thank you.
See this?
Had it up to here with your cynical bullshit. Get me access to that data.
S'all right. What's your name?
How did you get here?
How'd you get in here? They let you outta your room?
Well… I know a few tricks. My dad's a techie – he taught me a ton of stuff.
In the director's office? Come on, I know you were looking for something.
[Sit] You're too old to cry.
It's just, well… I'm gettin' old.
You? Old?
Soon no one'll want me, not even the worst teams. And Dad said I can't screw up 'cause we live in Dogtown and a career in sports is our last chance.
Yeah, s-sorta wanted to see if I got picked for a team! But... still no one.
It's not fair. I've got all the right skills, the right chrome, I'm super duper fast...
Tough, havin' that responsibility. But if it wasn't for your family, what would you want?
You're a good kid, Tommie, know that?
Listen, some things ain't worth the price. Can end up losin' everything. Trust me, I've been there.
entries.maleVariant: Listen, kid, some things ain't worth the price. Can end up losin' everything. Trust me, I've been there.

entries.femaleVariant: Yeah, clever little rascal.
Yes, ma'am – I-I just need to find, uh, uh… that thing…
entries.maleVariant: Yes, sir – I just need to find, uh… t-that thing…

entries.femaleVariant: Don't worry, Tommie.
Run along now, Tommie.
Run along now, Tommie. Hop to it.
entries.maleVariant: Now run along, Tommie. Hop to it.

entries.femaleVariant: It's OK, Tommie, don't gotta stay. Fiona and I need to talk grown-up stuff.
Right?
Uhh… that's right.
Now, run along, kiddo.
But… I didn't do nothin' wrong.
It's all right, Tommie. Go back to your room.
We're reasonable people – I'm sure we can work something out. What is it you want?
I need access to your computer.
To destroy everything I've just seen.
Password to the terminal and the data of every suit you've done biz with. Transactions, contracts, agreements. Whole enchilada.
Wanna burn this place to the fucking ground.
I have a duty to protect my business and my clients. You understand that, I'm sure.
Think of the children. Would you really deprive them of their only chance for a better life?
Just gets better 'n' better, this bitch…
If you'll please just hear me out, I'd like to make you an offer.
A-to-the-fuckin'-men.
I understand you're upset, but let's talk this through. You connected to a terminal containing my clients' data, correct?
Oh?
Get fucked.
You'll be destroying everything I've built.
That's the fucking idea. Access. Now.
Fine, here.
You'll regret this. Sooner than you think.
Come, let me show you something.
Portraits? Really?
Don't test my patience.
Posters and trophies? That supposed to convince me?
My patience is wearin' thin, Fiona.
Mark Elway, twenty-two years old, exceptional basketball player. Monica Diaz, twenty-five, ranked top fifteen worldwide in tennis.
And our brightest star – Al Ford. The NUSA's heavyweight champion at only twenty-one years old.
Guessin' I'm about to hear that this is all 'cause of you?
entries.maleVariant: Guessin' I'm about to hear this is all 'cause of you?

entries.femaleVariant: I helped them. Me. And if you leak my clients, this center will go under and these kids' bright future darken quick.
Why here in Dogtown?
How much're you makin' off these poor kids and their parents?
Why go to all this trouble?
Well... If you really want to know, ugh... It's cheaper.
Not 'cause you're chippin' kids that are too young for it?
Hah! You think we're the only ones? Name me one professional athlete without implants. You can’t.
Unlike your... "profession," I provide chances for a better life. Not for free, granted, but the parents know the risks. It's in their contracts.
Knowing and understanding – two different things.
Go to Night City – look at all those kids walking the streets, alone. Can you claim they're better off than our future athletes?
What are Tommie's chances of getting signed?
What're Tommie's chances of scorin' a contract?
Close to none. Out of the best players, only fifteen to twenty percent get signed. Tommie'll probably be going home.
'Thout any scratch to maintain his chrome, regulate his organs and keep his body functioning properly.
Transfer the data and let's get this "controlled leak" on the road.
OK, data transferred.
Come the fuck on, V. Really?
Done. Y-you take part of the data and Tommie gets into some local, European league. Won't be stardom, but it's still a dream come true.
It's about taxes.
I'm the one asking questions here.
Someone got tired of your clients not paying their dues.
Got it backwards. I'm the one asking questions.
You're using Tommie as a bargaining chip?
Your employer wants names, transaction details – they'll get 'em. Everyone walks away happy.
Here's my offer – we do a controlled leak. I'll hand over the data of a few clients of secondary importance to me.
Including Tommie. His file's right here. You help me, you help him.
You're usin' Tommie as a bargaining chip?
Barkin' up the wrong tree. Truth is, I don't care what happens to 'im.
We all have choices to make.
We'll do the leak, but Tommie gets signed.
I'll accept your offer, 'long as you make sure Tommie gets a contract. A good one.
Great, be seein' ya.
Uhhhh... Have some fun, I guess? Or take a vacation! That'd be neat.
Uh, what do you intend to do with it?
"Business"? Heh, the fuckin' gall…
I don't care about the kid.
Heard enough. The data – now.
Uh… I-I see.
That's how these things go. You either win big, or go home. But maybe you can still help Tommie – his file doesn't have to stay on my desk.
You're a real good Samaritan, huh?
The earlier you start, the better long term. Sports would be a snooze fest without them.
OK, well… I'm gonna head back... just please don't tell Miss Fiona you saw me?
I won't. Get outta here.
Those kids who end up on the street with post-op implant sickness, you don't think they hang their pics here, too, do you?
'S the kind of cynicism that deserves a medal. Cheap, plastic kind.
I know.
Hey, chin up, kiddo. It'll all work out, you'll see.
Uh, OK! I-I just need to check something first…
[Shake hand]
My hands are dirty enough.
Uhh. Data transferred. You made a wise decision.
Hands're dirty enough, thanks.
Place oughta burn with her inside it.
[Steal data]
